00:13:24,160 --> 00:13:26,460
运桨分四个步骤，先生们
There's four parts to a stroke, gentlemen,

194
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:27,830
不是三个，好吗？
not three, okay?

195
00:13:27,970 --> 00:13:30,270
入水，推进，完成，归位
Catch, drive, finish, and recovery.

196
00:13:30,840 --> 00:13:32,200
一个都不能少
You can't skip any of 'em.

197
00:13:32,470 --> 00:13:34,640
你们知道我们为什么没走直线吗？
And you know why we're not going in a straight line?

198
00:13:34,770 --> 00:13:36,110
因为22号
'Cause number 22 here

199
00:13:36,170 --> 00:13:38,210
是这里唯一一个在听我说话的人
is the only one that's listening to me.

200
00:13:39,110 --> 00:13:40,380
入水，推进
Catch, drive,

201
00:13:40,520 --> 00:13:41,620
完成，归位
finish, recovery.

202
00:13:41,750 --> 00:13:42,710
这样好多了
That's better.

203
00:13:43,120 --> 00:13:45,250
好的，让我们加快节奏到18拍
All right. Let's pick up the pace to 18.

204
00:13:45,380 --> 00:13:47,360
这里有很多好木材啊，教练
Lot of tall timber in this bunch, Coach.

205
00:13:47,940 --> 00:13:49,670
那边的孩子几乎没有能比得上你们校队的
Few boys there could even push your varsity crew.

206
00:13:49,740 --> 00:13:51,400
才第一天，还很难说呢
It's hard to judge off one day.

207
00:13:51,430 --> 00:13:52,730
不过，你还要看到什么
Still, you had to see enough

208
00:13:52,750 --> 00:13:54,530
才能让你开怀大笑？
to make you almost finally crack a smile?

209
00:13:54,560 --> 00:13:56,690
赛季结束后我会告诉你的，啊？
Yeah, I'll let you know at the end of the season, huh?

210
00:13:56,710 --> 00:13:57,630
奥运年，今年
Olympic year, this year,

211
00:13:57,650 --> 00:13:59,360
所以假如理想的话，他们的训练时间要比以往更长
so ideally, they'll stretch longer than most.

212
00:13:59,390 --> 00:14:01,190
奥运年？我都没有意识到
Olympic year? I didn't realize.

213
00:14:02,700 --> 00:14:04,060
我在加州大学和埃布莱特教练谈过了
I spoke with Coach Ebright down in Cali.

214
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:05,360
他肯定意识到了
He's sure aware of it.

215
00:14:05,450 --> 00:14:06,630
他对自己的机会也很有信心
Feels good about his chances, too.

216
00:14:06,670 --> 00:14:07,470
哦，是吗？
Oh, yeah?

217
00:14:07,490 --> 00:14:09,160
有什么第一印象想报道出来的吗？
Any first impressions you'd like to see in print?

218
00:14:09,190 --> 00:14:11,230
你知道我不看报纸的，洛伊尔
You know I don't read the paper, Royal.

219
00:14:11,270 --> 00:14:12,580
对不起，教练
Excuse me, Coach.

220
00:14:12,660 --> 00:14:14,150
如果你想问诀窍，那就与其他人一样
If you're looking for tips, you're gonna have to get 'em

221
00:14:14,170 --> 00:14:15,530
在训练中去找吧
in practice like everybody else.

222
00:14:15,560 --> 00:14:17,740
不，先生，我只是想知道会给多少工资
No, sir. I was just wondering how much this paid.

223
00:14:17,930 --> 00:14:18,850
再说一遍？
Say again?

224
00:14:18,890 --> 00:14:21,140
他们说，如果能入选，还能得到一份工作？
They said there was a job included if you make the team?

225
00:14:21,190 --> 00:14:22,290
我只想知道够不够支付
I just need to know if it's gonna cover

226
00:14:22,320 --> 00:14:23,450
我剩下的学费
the rest of my tuition.

227
00:14:24,120 --> 00:14:26,490
是的，我肯定是够的
Yeah, I'm sure it will.

228
00:14:27,270 --> 00:14:30,100
嘿，你先集中精力看能不能入选吧，孩子
Hey, you just concentrate for now on making the squad, son.

229
00:14:30,140 --> 00:14:31,100
谢谢你，先生
Thank you, sir.

230
00:14:35,300 --> 00:14:36,540
现在，我打赌这个问题
Now, there's a question I bet

231
00:14:36,560 --> 00:14:38,340
那些常春藤联盟的教练们永远也不会遇到
those Ivy League coaches never get.

232
00:14:38,470 --> 00:14:39,570
说到
Speakin' of,

233
00:14:39,650 --> 00:14:41,350
我当然希望今年能比去年更好
I sure hope this year goes better than the last.

234
00:14:41,540 --> 00:14:43,400
没有人比我更支持你的孩子们了
No one's rooting for your boys more than me.

235
00:14:44,410 --> 00:14:46,740
－祝你好运，教练　－你也是，洛伊尔
- Good luck, Coach. - And you, Royal.

236
00:14:48,520 --> 00:14:49,830
你去吃东西吗？
Did you go grab some food?

237
00:14:49,880 --> 00:14:51,210
啊，我不饿
Ah, I'm not hungry.

238
00:14:51,710 --> 00:14:53,450
如果你想要吃的话，我拿的足够我们俩吃的
I got enough for us both if you want it.

239
00:14:53,510 --> 00:14:54,590
没那么饿
Not that hungry.

240
00:15:00,090 --> 00:15:01,460
回头见
I'll see you later.

241
00:15:11,770 --> 00:15:13,100
我很感激
I appreciate it.

242
00:15:24,010 --> 00:15:25,350
给你
There you go.

243
00:15:27,510 --> 00:15:29,520
－给你，先生　－谢谢
- Here you go, sir. - Thank you.

244
00:15:41,110 --> 00:15:43,450
鸡肉怎么样？
How's your chicken?

245
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:45,570
很不错，谢谢
Great. Thanks.

246
00:15:46,330 --> 00:15:48,230
是吗，你吃的是猪排
Yeah, that's a pork chop you're eating.

247
00:15:50,260 --> 00:15:51,490
啊
Ah.

248
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:54,270
对不起
Sorry.

249
00:15:55,510 --> 00:15:57,940
所以，我今天见到了洛伊尔・布鲁姆
So, I saw Royal Brougham today.

250
00:15:58,200 --> 00:15:59,500
他还特意告诉我
And he made sure to tell me

251
00:15:59,520 --> 00:16:02,330
凯・埃布莱特的球队今年实力强劲
that Ky Ebright's squad is strong this year.

252
00:16:03,110 --> 00:16:04,790
加州大学队一直很强的
Cal is always strong.

253
00:16:05,790 --> 00:16:07,890
而你一直在担心
And you always worry.

254
00:16:10,710 --> 00:16:12,380
这帮新孩子们看起来怎么样？
How'd your new boys look?

255
00:16:13,120 --> 00:16:15,220
现在下结论还为时过早
Well, it's too early to say.

256
00:16:15,590 --> 00:16:17,180
人倒是有很多
There's definitely a lot of 'em.

257
00:16:17,310 --> 00:16:19,710
很好，有这么大的马场可供选择
That's good. Nice big stable to choose from.

258
00:16:19,830 --> 00:16:22,360
－如果有足够多的能坚持到最后　－最好的就会
- If enough of them last. - The best ones will.

259
00:16:23,080 --> 00:16:25,010
－就像你一样　－嗯
- Just like you did. - Mm.

260
00:16:45,770 --> 00:16:46,890
你怎么了？
What's wrong with you?

261
00:16:47,680 --> 00:16:49,420
没什么，只是有点僵硬
Nothing, just a little stiff.

262
00:16:49,440 --> 00:16:50,710
嗯，看到了，怎么搞的？
Yeah, looks it. How come?

263
00:16:50,730 --> 00:16:52,440
划艇划到我们差点没命
Rowed boats till it almost killed us.

264
00:16:53,170 --> 00:16:53,900
什么？
What?

265
00:16:53,930 --> 00:16:56,270
课本第43页
Page 43 in your texts.

266
00:16:58,190 --> 00:17:01,120
因此，在解决框架问题时
So, in solving the framework,

267
00:17:01,310 --> 00:17:03,690
反射意味着什么？
what does it mean to reflect?

268
00:17:21,250 --> 00:17:22,950
对不起，年轻人
Excuse me, young man.

269
00:17:23,180 --> 00:17:26,120
要不要我小声点，好让你休息？
Would you like me to speak quieter so you can rest?

270
00:17:26,890 --> 00:17:29,160
我感觉这可能是个陷阱问题
I feel like that's maybe a trick question.

271
00:17:29,270 --> 00:17:30,840
－安静
- Quiet!

272
00:17:31,450 --> 00:17:32,710
要么专心听讲，要么回家睡觉
Pay attention or go home to sleep.

273
00:17:32,730 --> 00:17:34,240
你不能在这睡大觉
You can't do both in here.

274
00:17:37,600 --> 00:17:39,200
不客气，乔・兰茨
You're welcome, Joe Rantz.

275
00:17:39,260 --> 00:17:40,500
谢谢
Thank you.

276
00:17:52,930 --> 00:17:54,500
三
Three.

277
00:17:54,630 --> 00:17:55,390
四
Four.

278
00:17:55,530 --> 00:17:57,930
推，然后拉，推...
Push, then pull. Push...

279
00:17:58,170 --> 00:17:59,600
起，躺
Up, down!

280
00:18:04,700 --> 00:18:06,170
48号和12号在艇头
48 and 12 on the bow.

281
00:18:06,310 --> 00:18:08,480
是的，我想...
Yeah. I'm thinkin'...

282
00:18:13,420 --> 00:18:16,180
把莫里斯放在兰茨身后的六号位？
What about Morris in the six behind Rantz?

283
00:18:36,270 --> 00:18:37,570
跟上我的节奏
Keep time with me.

284
00:18:37,710 --> 00:18:40,840
一，二，三，四，一，二...
Stroke, two, three, four. Stroke, two...

285
00:19:11,210 --> 00:19:13,580
来吧，孩子们！谁更想要？
Come on, boys! Who wants it more?

286
00:19:17,610 --> 00:19:19,340
继续蹬腿
Keep driving those legs!

287
00:19:19,480 --> 00:19:22,250
不要让22号打败你！
Do not let 22 beat you!

288
00:19:46,040 --> 00:19:47,310
你还记得我吗？
You still remember me?

289
00:19:48,100 --> 00:19:49,410
嗯
Mm-hmm.

290
00:19:50,120 --> 00:19:51,150
不确定
Wasn't sure.

291
00:19:51,230 --> 00:19:52,460
最近很少见到你
Haven't seen you much lately.

292
00:19:52,590 --> 00:19:54,330
我只是一直在忙事情
I just been busy with stuff.

293
00:19:54,570 --> 00:19:56,110
－赛艇？－大部分是
- Rowing stuff? - Mostly.

294
00:19:56,230 --> 00:19:57,590
嗯
Hmm.

295
00:19:57,620 --> 00:19:59,400
我听罗杰说，他们今天要公布队员名单
I heard Roger say that they're announcing the team today.

296
00:19:59,420 --> 00:20:00,590
你能进吗？
Are you gonna make it?

297
00:20:01,050 --> 00:20:02,920
有很多人都想进
There's lot of guys tryin'.

298
00:20:05,100 --> 00:20:07,670
等你进了，你想带我去坐艇兜风吗？
You wanna take me on a boat ride when you do?

299
00:20:08,560 --> 00:20:09,760
当然
Sure.

300
00:20:19,180 --> 00:20:20,380
先生们
Gentlemen, 

301
00:20:20,980 --> 00:20:22,740
感谢大家参与
I wanna thank you all for comin' out

302
00:20:22,820 --> 00:20:24,560
并全力以赴
and giving your best effort.

303
00:20:26,430 --> 00:20:28,620
你们留在这里的每一个人
Every single one of you left standing

304
00:20:28,730 --> 00:20:30,270
都有令人钦佩的表现
has performed admirably.

305
00:20:31,330 --> 00:20:35,060
遗憾的是，你们中只有少数人可以被选中留下来继续
Unfortunately, only a few of you can be chosen to continue.

306
00:20:36,090 --> 00:20:37,330
博尔斯教练
Coach Bolles.

307
00:20:40,930 --> 00:20:41,930
休谟
Hume.

308
00:20:43,680 --> 00:20:44,890
亨特
Hunt.

309
00:20:47,590 --> 00:20:49,090
麦克米伦
McMillin.

310
00:20:53,600 --> 00:20:54,870
戴
Day.

311
00:20:55,680 --> 00:20:57,520
莫里斯
Morris.

312
00:20:58,520 --> 00:20:59,720
怀特
White.

313
00:21:01,670 --> 00:21:02,710
亚当
Adam.

314
00:21:05,330 --> 00:21:06,670
兰茨
Rantz.

315
00:21:11,490 --> 00:21:13,320
科伊，你是替补
Coy, you're the reserve.

316
00:21:14,020 --> 00:21:16,820
感谢你们付出的时间和努力
We thank the rest of you for your time and your effort.

317
00:21:20,440 --> 00:21:21,840
那好吧
All right, then.

318
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:24,310
去庆祝吧
Go and celebrate.

319
00:21:25,170 --> 00:21:27,170
明天水上见
I will see you on the water tomorrow.

320
00:21:27,750 --> 00:21:28,920
干得好
Well done.

321
00:21:49,440 --> 00:21:50,940
这是我最喜欢的部分
That's my favorite part.

322
00:21:54,130 --> 00:21:55,250
来吧，孩子们
Come on, boys.

323
00:21:56,180 --> 00:21:57,710
我们走吧
Let's go.

324
00:21:58,820 --> 00:22:00,260
现在把浆举起来
Now lift 'em up.

325
00:22:13,700 --> 00:22:15,470
这家伙满嘴都是他的道奇
It's all this guy talks about, his Dodge.

326
00:22:18,880 --> 00:22:20,740
嘿，听着，我划得太多了
Hey, listen, I've done so much rowing.

327
00:22:21,470 --> 00:22:22,650
我就知道你会入选的
I knew you'd made it.

328
00:22:22,670 --> 00:22:23,920
我很高兴我们中有个人做到了
I'm glad one of us did.

329
00:22:23,940 --> 00:22:25,340
啊，你的入选一直都是稳的
Ah, you were always in the bag.

330
00:22:25,360 --> 00:22:26,940
当教练叫到我的名字时，我的膝盖差点跪下了
When Coach called my name, my knees almost buckled.

331
00:22:26,970 --> 00:22:28,470
不知道他们会给我们安排什么位置
I wonder what seats they'll put us in.

332
00:22:28,500 --> 00:22:29,660
我只想坐在领桨手的位置上
I just want the stroke.

333
00:22:29,710 --> 00:22:31,640
那是休姆的位置，我打包票
That's Hume's seat. Guaranteed.

334
00:22:31,770 --> 00:22:33,140
嘿，你不是哑巴吧？
Hey, you're not a mute, are you?

335
00:22:33,210 --> 00:22:35,240
因为我从没听你说过一句话
'Cause I've never once heard you say nothin'.

336
00:22:35,540 --> 00:22:36,450
不是
No.

337
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:38,320
像他那样划桨，他不需要会说话
He doesn't need to talk, the way he pulls that oar.

338
00:22:38,340 --> 00:22:39,850
是啊，查克，也许你应该多划桨少说话
Yeah, Chuck, maybe you should pull more and talk less,

339
00:22:39,880 --> 00:22:41,120
如果你想坐那个领桨手座位
you want that stroke seat.

340
00:22:41,150 --> 00:22:42,400
我不在乎他们把我放在哪里
I don't care where they put me,

341
00:22:42,430 --> 00:22:43,610
只要我在就行
as long as I'm in there somewhere.

342
00:22:43,710 --> 00:22:45,030
我们都会在的
We're all in there somewhere.

343
00:22:45,060 --> 00:22:46,290
是啊
Yeah.

344
00:22:46,430 --> 00:22:48,550
向华盛顿鞠躬
Bow down to Washington

345
