00:24:50,290 --> 00:24:53,270
罗杰，矮子和其他一些人
Roger, Shorty, some others.

380
00:24:55,020 --> 00:24:57,220
你知道，他们会在广播里播报比赛
You know, they put the races on the radio.

381
00:24:57,650 --> 00:24:58,950
每个人都在听
Everybody listens.

382
00:24:59,370 --> 00:25:01,340
他们拍了一些照片
Yeah, they took, uh, some photos.

383
00:25:02,080 --> 00:25:04,850
－问了一堆问题　－什么样的问题？
- Asked a bunch of questions. - What kinds of questions?

384
00:25:04,870 --> 00:25:06,040
就是，你知道
It's just, you know,

385
00:25:06,060 --> 00:25:07,620
我们来自哪里，诸如此类的
where we're from, stuff like that.

386
00:25:08,260 --> 00:25:09,840
你告诉他们事实了吗？
Did you tell them the truth?

387
00:25:10,630 --> 00:25:12,420
嗯，差不多吧
Mm. Mostly.

388
00:25:18,410 --> 00:25:20,150
你们都会出名的
You're all gonna be famous.

389
00:25:21,220 --> 00:25:23,420
然后你就真的会忘记我了
Then you really will forget about me.

390
00:25:28,730 --> 00:25:30,660
就算我想，我觉得我也做不到
I don't think I could if I tried.

391
00:25:47,990 --> 00:25:49,550
你得把我们划回岸上
You get to row us back to shore.

392
00:25:49,580 --> 00:25:50,970
我们早上还有课
We have class in the morning.

393
00:26:08,110 --> 00:26:10,300
－你想要哪张床？－我不在乎
- Which bed you want? - Couldn't care less.

394
00:26:15,840 --> 00:26:17,670
哦，不错
Oh, nice.

395
00:26:17,880 --> 00:26:19,510
我们可以留着这些，对吗？
We get to keep these, right?

396
00:26:19,710 --> 00:26:21,540
只要我们还在队里
Long as we stay on the team.

397
00:26:26,380 --> 00:26:28,620
艇上的每个座位都有自己的用途
Each seat on the boat has its own purpose.

398
00:26:28,830 --> 00:26:31,950
就像一匹高大赛马身上的8个独立部位
Like eight separate parts of one great racehorse.

399
00:26:32,210 --> 00:26:34,740
莫里斯在一号，戴在二号
Morris in one, Day in two,

400
00:26:35,160 --> 00:26:36,490
亚当在三号
and Adam in the three.

401
00:26:36,520 --> 00:26:39,360
你们的技术要让艇保持正确的航向
Your technique will keep the boat on its proper course.

402
00:26:39,730 --> 00:26:42,110
而四，五，六就像是引擎舱
And four, five, and six are like the engine room.

403
00:26:42,240 --> 00:26:43,580
这是力量源泉
That is the power.

404
00:26:43,610 --> 00:26:46,030
怀特，麦克米伦和亨特
White, McMillin, and Hunt.

405
00:26:46,240 --> 00:26:48,340
现在，兰茨是我们的七号
Now, Rantz is our seven.

406
00:26:48,620 --> 00:26:51,160
所以，你和休姆，领桨员，一起设定节奏
So, you set the pace with Hume, the stroke.

407
00:26:51,710 --> 00:26:55,220
每一匹好赛马都有一个骑师
And every good racehorse has a jockey.

408
00:26:56,220 --> 00:26:57,580
格伦・莫里...
Glenn Morry...

409
00:26:57,940 --> 00:26:59,210
来吧，格伦
Come on, Glenn.

410
00:27:00,570 --> 00:27:02,040
是我们的舵手
is our coxswain.

411
00:27:03,290 --> 00:27:04,930
现在，他指挥的策略
Now, he calls the strategy

412
00:27:04,950 --> 00:27:07,210
是由我和博尔斯教练设定的
set up by myself and Coach Bolles.

413
00:27:07,730 --> 00:27:09,830
他想让你们跑的时候，就会给你们松缰绳
He'll give you rein when he wants you to run,

414
00:27:09,880 --> 00:27:12,000
他会把缰绳拉紧，让你们慢下来
he'll pull you back to slow you down.

415
00:27:12,190 --> 00:27:15,390
一旦时机成熟，他就会拿出鞭子
And when the time is right, he'll get out his whip.

416
00:27:15,830 --> 00:27:17,840
嘿，伙计们
Hey, fellas.

417
00:27:18,060 --> 00:27:19,730
好了，该下水了
Okay, time to get in the water.

418
00:28:03,970 --> 00:28:05,400
我们再来一次！
Let's go again!

419
00:28:10,180 --> 00:28:11,890
嘿，菜鸟队
Hey, junior boat,

420
00:28:12,160 --> 00:28:13,790
第一天，累吗？
you tired after your first day?

421
00:28:15,370 --> 00:28:17,170
他不会成功的，别这么认真
He'll never make it. Don't take it so hard.

422
00:28:17,190 --> 00:28:19,030
嘿，你去哪儿？回来
Hey, where you going? Come back.

423
00:28:22,260 --> 00:28:23,830
我讨厌那些混蛋
I hate those assholes.

424
00:28:24,240 --> 00:28:26,300
你得学会掌握自己的节奏
You gotta learn to pace yourself.

425
00:29:06,980 --> 00:29:09,610
－乔，对吧？　－嗯哼
- It's Joe, isn't it? - Mm-hmm.

426
00:29:10,690 --> 00:29:14,480
你们大多数人都对艇不感兴趣
Most of you boys don't have an interest in a boat

427
00:29:14,510 --> 00:29:15,870
直到你坐在里面
until you can sit in it.

428
00:29:17,630 --> 00:29:19,410
你喜欢做木工活吗？
You like to work with wood?

429
00:29:19,890 --> 00:29:21,590
是的，我父亲做过一些
Yeah, my father did some.

430
00:29:21,810 --> 00:29:23,310
他以前会做些东西
He used to make things.

431
00:29:24,240 --> 00:29:26,700
不是这种，就是门廊之类的东西
Nothing like this, just porches and stuff.

432
00:29:29,110 --> 00:29:31,450
有一次，我帮他修好了一艘旧独木舟
I helped him fix up an old canoe once.

433
00:29:32,410 --> 00:29:35,780
我相信他和你的母亲现在一定为你感到非常骄傲
I'm sure he and your mother must be very proud of you now.

434
00:29:36,640 --> 00:29:38,210
加入赛艇队
Making the team.

435
00:29:45,430 --> 00:29:46,860
这是给你们的
This is for you boys.

436
00:29:50,420 --> 00:29:52,520
你们的比赛艇
Your racing shell.

437
00:29:53,900 --> 00:29:56,120
随时欢迎你来帮我一把
Always welcome to give me a hand with it.

438
00:29:56,330 --> 00:29:58,270
如果你有空的话
If you find some free time.

439
00:30:08,030 --> 00:30:10,030
不，我不是说现在
No, I didn't mean right now.

440
00:30:10,100 --> 00:30:11,880
你今晚应该好好休息
You should rest up tonight.

441
00:30:11,930 --> 00:30:13,140
我没事
I'm okay.

442
00:30:18,450 --> 00:30:21,520
技术比力量更重要
Technique is more important than power.

443
00:30:21,830 --> 00:30:24,310
你必须学会划出完美的桨法
You have to be able to pull a perfect oar, 

444
00:30:24,340 --> 00:30:26,440
一桨接着一桨
stroke after stroke.

445
00:30:27,040 --> 00:30:28,520
所谓摇摆
It's called swing.

446
00:30:28,940 --> 00:30:31,960
当8个人全都划得如此整齐划一
When all eight are rowing in such perfect unison

447
00:30:31,990 --> 00:30:33,620
没有任何一个动作
that no single action

448
00:30:33,870 --> 00:30:36,560
和艇上其他人的不同步
is out of sync with the rest of the boat.

449
00:30:36,690 --> 00:30:38,730
这样你们的力量就不会互相抵消了
Then you aren't fighting each other.

450
00:30:38,770 --> 00:30:40,770
艇跑起来更省力
You're moving with less effort.

451
00:30:41,210 --> 00:30:42,640
你划出的每一桨都相当于
Each one of your strokes is worth

452
00:30:42,660 --> 00:30:44,700
另一艘艇的一桨半
one and a half of the other boat's.

453
00:30:45,450 --> 00:30:47,420
大多数艇员从未领略过
Most crews never find it.

454
00:30:47,670 --> 00:30:49,380
但当他们领略到时
But when they do, 

455
00:30:49,400 --> 00:30:52,630
赛艇与其说是一项运动，不如说是一首诗
rowing is more poetry than sport.

456
00:30:53,810 --> 00:30:57,070
怀特和戴，交换位置
White and Day, switch.

457
00:30:59,310 --> 00:31:01,340
兰茨，亚当
Rantz, Adam,

458
00:31:02,050 --> 00:31:03,390
换回来
switch back.

459
00:31:07,020 --> 00:31:08,220
划！
Row!

460
00:31:08,560 --> 00:31:09,560
划！
Row!

461
00:31:09,860 --> 00:31:11,020
－划！－来吧
- Row! - Come on!

462
00:31:11,320 --> 00:31:12,930
－划！－来吧
- Row! - Come on!

463
00:31:13,670 --> 00:31:15,300
划！划过湖面
Row! Row through the lake!

464
00:31:15,320 --> 00:31:16,860
划！用力
Row! More!

465
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:18,510
怎么，你们把最近三年学过的东西
What, did you forget everything you learned

466
00:31:18,540 --> 00:31:19,970
都忘了吗？
in the last three years?

467
00:31:20,480 --> 00:31:22,410
布朗，你还在划空
Brown, you're still skying.

468
00:31:23,140 --> 00:31:25,700
比林斯，你是领桨员吗？你在赶
Billings, are you the stroke? You're rushing.

469
00:31:25,810 --> 00:31:28,540
你身后有七个人，都被你带得很赶
You have seven men behind you, all chasing the boat.

470
00:31:29,140 --> 00:31:30,360
34桨
34 strokes.

471
00:31:30,440 --> 00:31:32,000
你们划34桨没问题
You're fine at 34 strokes.

472
00:31:32,220 --> 00:31:34,010
再高一点，你们就崩溃了
Anything higher and you fall apart.

473
00:31:34,220 --> 00:31:36,140
34桨，你们赢不了加州大学
34 strokes, you don't beat Cal.

474
00:31:36,310 --> 00:31:37,450
34桨
34 strokes,

475
00:31:37,500 --> 00:31:39,130
在波基普西你们赢不了
you don't win at Poughkeepsie.

476
00:31:39,790 --> 00:31:41,660
你们肯定去不了德国
You certainly don't get to Germany.

477
00:31:42,070 --> 00:31:44,710
你们知道34桨能打败谁吗？
You know who you beat with 34 strokes?

478
00:31:45,240 --> 00:31:46,650
初级队
The JV boat.

479
00:31:46,670 --> 00:31:47,670
只是可能
Maybe.

480
00:31:48,670 --> 00:31:51,270
你们还在等什么？回到艇上去
What are you guys waiting for? Get back in the boat.

481
00:31:52,720 --> 00:31:54,750
你们，你们要回到那里去
You guys, you're gonna get back out there

482
00:31:54,870 --> 00:31:57,810
然后再做一次，直到做对为止！
and you're gonna do it again until you get it right!

483
00:31:58,550 --> 00:32:00,710
希望我没有打扰你，艾尔
Hope I'm not intruding, Al.

484
00:32:00,930 --> 00:32:03,640
不，本，进来吧，请坐
Not at all, Ben. Come on in. Take a seat.

485
00:32:03,930 --> 00:32:05,060
正是时候
Great timing.

486
00:32:05,390 --> 00:32:07,050
刚好在查看准备送交贵委员会的
Just going through the equipment budget

487
00:32:07,090 --> 00:32:08,480
设备预算
to send over to your committee.

488
00:32:09,260 --> 00:32:10,390
没什么不合理的
Nothing unreasonable.

489
00:32:10,410 --> 00:32:12,350
体育馆的一些部分
Some pieces for the gymnasium.

490
00:32:13,190 --> 00:32:14,480
还有五年前的制服
And the five-year-old uniforms

491
00:32:14,500 --> 00:32:15,840
看起来有点破旧
are startin' to look a little ragged.

492
00:32:15,860 --> 00:32:17,220
啊，我们会尽力的
Ah, we'll see what we can do.

493
00:32:17,570 --> 00:32:19,000
委员会下周要开会
Committee's meeting next week.

494
00:32:19,190 --> 00:32:22,230
赢得越多通常意味着校友资助就越多
More wins usually means more money from the alumni.

495
00:32:22,250 --> 00:32:23,350
当然
Sure.

496
00:32:23,960 --> 00:32:25,520
我们的小伙子们怎么样了，教练？
So, how are our boys doing, Coach?

497
00:32:25,680 --> 00:32:27,660
现在说还为时尚早，但很可靠
Early to say, but solid.

498
00:32:27,680 --> 00:32:28,900
哦，他们一直在努力训练
Oh, they've been workin' hard.

499
00:32:28,940 --> 00:32:30,110
我儿子，波，他们整个休赛期
My boy, Bo, had 'em training

500
00:32:30,140 --> 00:32:31,540
－都在训练　－嗯
- all off season. - Hmm.

501
00:32:31,750 --> 00:32:33,430
我认为他们今年会向加州大学发起真正的冲击
Think they're gonna make a real run at Cal this year.

502
00:32:33,460 --> 00:32:34,790
我希望我们能做到
I hope we can.

503
00:32:34,840 --> 00:32:36,700
我们也有一个不错的初级队在训练，你应该...
We got a good junior boat to push 'em, too. You should...

504
00:32:36,720 --> 00:32:39,320
如果可以在我们这挂上横幅，而不是让加州大学
It'd be nice to finally hang a banner up at our place

505
00:32:39,630 --> 00:32:41,800
把它们都拿走，那就太好了
instead of letting Cal have 'em all.

506
00:32:42,010 --> 00:32:43,380
我们会尽力的，先生
We'll do our best, sir.

507
00:32:43,430 --> 00:32:45,300
还有一枚奥运奖牌可以拼一拼
And an Olympic medal to go with it.

508
00:32:45,430 --> 00:32:47,100
波说他们队有机会
Bo says his boat's got a shot.

509
00:32:47,120 --> 00:32:48,690
如果我们加把劲
If we work hard.

510
00:32:48,920 --> 00:32:50,250
并取得一些突破
And catch some breaks.

511
00:32:50,300 --> 00:32:52,700
教练，人生的突破都是赢家自己创造的
Winners make our own breaks in life, Coach.

512
00:32:53,340 --> 00:32:54,670
我们需要这个
And we need this.

513
00:32:55,260 --> 00:32:56,560
机不可失，时不再来
It's now or never.

514
00:32:58,180 --> 00:32:59,490
嗯
Hmm.

515
00:33:06,680 --> 00:33:09,250
如果我们这些影子冒犯了你
If we shadows have offended

516
00:33:09,280 --> 00:33:11,880
那么只需想象，这一切都是梦境
Think but this, and all is mended.

517
00:33:12,350 --> 00:33:14,280
你只是在这里打了个盹...
That you have but slumbered here...

518
00:33:14,610 --> 00:33:17,580
而这些幻象就出现了
While these visions did appear.

519
00:33:17,700 --> 00:33:18,540
谢谢
Thank you.

520
00:33:19,830 --> 00:33:22,290
是一个叫莎士比亚的，对吗？
It's some fella called Shakespeare, right?

521
00:33:22,630 --> 00:33:23,830
你知道，搞音乐的
You know, music people

522
00:33:23,860 --> 00:33:25,600
他们应该收拾好自己的垃圾
should have to take care of their own trash.

523
00:33:25,630 --> 00:33:27,130
比昨晚自助餐厅好多了
Better than the cafeteria last night.

524
00:33:27,240 --> 00:33:29,060
我是说，天哪，我今天差点吃不下饭
I mean, God, I almost couldn't eat today.

525
00:33:29,140 --> 00:33:31,550
你看到那些食物了吗，都被弄成那样了？
You see that old food, all mushed around like that?

526
00:33:32,630 --> 00:33:34,000
你有没有注意到女孩们的桌子下面
You ever notice how under the girls' tables,

527
00:33:34,030 --> 00:33:35,340
总是最糟糕的？
it's always the worst?

528
00:33:35,540 --> 00:33:37,880
你仔细看，女孩们都很邋遢
When you look close, girls are nasty.

529
00:33:38,120 --> 00:33:40,590
你没发现，只是因为她们穿着漂亮的裙子
You don't realize it 'cause of their nice dresses

530
00:33:40,650 --> 00:33:42,220
头发都梳得好好的
and their hair's all fixed up.

531
00:33:42,340 --> 00:33:44,900
但我宁愿清理10个男孩的桌子下面，也不...
But I'll clean under 10 boys' tables before I do one...

532
00:33:49,660 --> 00:33:51,560
哦，唐，还有什么是你不会的吗？
Oh, Don, there anything you can't do?

533
00:33:54,930 --> 00:33:56,030
继续弹啊
Keep goin'.

534
00:34:04,250 --> 00:34:06,550
我们玩得开心吗？
Ain't we got fun?

535
00:34:07,240 --> 00:34:10,000
房租还没付呢，亲爱的
The rent's unpaid, dear

536
00:34:10,640 --> 00:34:12,610
我们没有车
We haven't a car

537
00:34:13,210 --> 00:34:16,120
无论如何，亲爱的
In any way, dear

538
00:34:16,330 --> 00:34:18,750
我们乐天知命
We'll stay as we are

539
00:34:20,030 --> 00:34:23,190
即使我们欠杂货店老板的钱
Even if we owe the grocer

540
00:34:23,540 --> 00:34:25,330
我们玩得开心吗？
Ain't we got fun?

541
00:34:25,440 --> 00:34:28,500
莫里斯在兰茨身后的六号位怎么样？
What about Morris in the six behind Rantz

542
00:34:28,830 --> 00:34:29,840
让亨特在一号位？
and Hunt in the one?

543
00:34:29,860 --> 00:34:31,430
我们上周试过了
We tried that last week.

544
00:34:31,580 --> 00:34:33,310
我不知道
I don't know.

545
00:34:33,470 --> 00:34:35,040
从纸面上看，这应该是可行的
On paper, this should work.

546
00:34:35,170 --> 00:34:36,500
不止是可行
Better than just work.

547
00:34:36,530 --> 00:34:38,660
你让他们和其他100个孩子进行单人比赛
You put them in singles against 100 other kids,

548
00:34:38,680 --> 00:34:40,780
我敢打赌，前8名的选手都在这里
I'd bet on that being the top eight finishers out there.

549
00:34:40,810 --> 00:34:42,000
这就是问题所在
That's the problem.

550
00:34:42,020 --> 00:34:43,320
他们很难记住
They have a hard time remembering

551
00:34:43,360 --> 00:34:45,170
他们不是在参加双桨比赛，尤其是兰茨
they aren't in sculls, especially Rantz.

552
00:34:45,260 --> 00:34:46,750
他们是我在这里见过的
They're a strong a group as I've ever seen

553
00:34:46,780 --> 00:34:47,800
最强大的队伍
come through here

554
00:34:47,830 --> 00:34:50,450
他们可能也是我见过的最糟糕的艇员
and they might also be the worst crew I've ever seen.

555
00:34:51,660 --> 00:34:53,430
这是一个糟糕的组合
It's a bad mix.

556
00:34:53,460 --> 00:34:54,640
是我的错
It's my fault.

557
00:34:54,660 --> 00:34:56,750
也许这些名字并不是问题所在
Well, maybe those names aren't the problem.

558
00:34:59,240 --> 00:35:02,320
有时，年轻的马匹需要一个声音更大的骑师
Sometimes young horses need a louder jockey.

559
00:35:15,550 --> 00:35:17,180
－你想见我，教练？
- You wanted to see me, Coach?

560
00:35:17,270 --> 00:35:18,900
关上门
Close the door.

