我们绝不能让那些有钱的混蛋代替我们去
No way we let those rich pricks go instead of us.

1483
01:30:39,900 --> 01:30:41,730
那我们最好找点钱出来
Then we better find some money.

1484
01:30:42,380 --> 01:30:43,490
是啊
Yeah.

1485
01:30:49,290 --> 01:30:50,680
艾尔，你去哪儿？
Al, where you goin'?

1486
01:31:06,030 --> 01:31:07,370
帮助将哈士奇队送往柏林
Help send the Huskies to Berlin.

1487
01:31:07,430 --> 01:31:08,590
谢谢，祝您愉快
Thank you. You have a nice day.

1488
01:31:08,640 --> 01:31:09,980
－谢谢　－好的
- Thank you, sir. - Sure.

1489
01:31:10,120 --> 01:31:11,310
嘿，伙计们
Hey, guys.

1490
01:31:11,550 --> 01:31:13,070
奥运赛艇队需要您的帮助才能到达柏林
The Olympic rowing team needs your help to get to Berlin.

1491
01:31:13,150 --> 01:31:14,470
我们只剩下几天时间了
We only got a couple days left.

1492
01:31:14,580 --> 01:31:15,980
伙计们，我有一块钱
Fellas, I got a dollar.

1493
01:31:16,090 --> 01:31:18,690
捐助几块钱，帮助我们打败德国人
Spare a couple dollars. Help us beat the Germans.

1494
01:31:20,920 --> 01:31:22,190
好的
All right.

1495
01:31:23,930 --> 01:31:25,630
谢谢，我叫罗杰
Thanks. My name's Roger.

1496
01:31:25,710 --> 01:31:26,740
嘿，我是查克
Hey, I'm Chuck.

1497
01:31:26,830 --> 01:31:27,860
哦，拜托
Oh, please.

1498
01:31:29,200 --> 01:31:30,870
好吧，你的时间不多了，教练
Well, you're running out of days, Coach.

1499
01:31:30,960 --> 01:31:33,050
－你还缺多少，4000？　－3000
- You have what, four left? - Three.

1500
01:31:33,180 --> 01:31:34,750
我们的资金才募集到了
And we've only gotten halfway

1501
01:31:34,780 --> 01:31:36,920
奥委会说的一半
to what the Olympic Committee says we need.

1502
01:31:37,050 --> 01:31:38,250
所以，如果你筹不足钱
So, if you don't raise the money, 

1503
01:31:38,280 --> 01:31:39,710
你们就得回西雅图去
you go back to Seattle

1504
01:31:39,750 --> 01:31:41,210
与此同时，其他队会去柏林？
while some other team goes to Berlin?

1505
01:31:41,250 --> 01:31:42,720
正确，这有悖于
Correct. And that goes against

1506
01:31:42,740 --> 01:31:44,420
一切体育精神
everything sports should be about.

1507
01:31:44,580 --> 01:31:47,090
运动员应该因为表现而得到奖励
Athletes should be rewarded for performance.

1508
01:31:47,150 --> 01:31:48,240
不搞政治
No politics,

1509
01:31:48,350 --> 01:31:50,320
不搞加分，或者
no adjusted scoring or selection

1510
01:31:50,460 --> 01:31:52,260
基于财富和地位来选人
based on wealth and standing.

1511
01:31:52,390 --> 01:31:53,960
让最优秀的人获胜
May the best man win.

1512
01:31:54,050 --> 01:31:55,940
他们是这么说的，就应该是这样
That's what they say. That's what it should be.

1513
01:31:56,010 --> 01:31:58,710
这些孩子，华盛顿的孩子
These boys, Washington's boys,

1514
01:31:59,180 --> 01:32:00,650
这个国家的孩子
this country's boys,

1515
01:32:00,670 --> 01:32:01,970
我的孩子
my boys,

1516
01:32:02,060 --> 01:32:05,100
他们已经证明了自己是最棒的
they have proven themselves to be the best.

1517
01:32:08,310 --> 01:32:10,070
帮助我们将哈士奇队送往柏林
Help us send the Huskies to Berlin.

1518
01:32:10,170 --> 01:32:12,180
提醒各位，一点一滴都是帮助
A reminder, folks, every little bit helps.

1519
01:32:12,310 --> 01:32:13,540
非常感谢
Thank you so much.

1520
01:32:13,710 --> 01:32:14,700
来吧，支持我们的孩子
Come on, support our boys.

1521
01:32:14,800 --> 01:32:16,070
好的，非常感谢
All right. Thank you so much.

1522
01:32:16,210 --> 01:32:18,310
非常感谢
Thank you so much.

1523
01:32:19,010 --> 01:32:20,910
非常感谢，谢谢
Thank you so much. Thank you.

1524
01:32:39,180 --> 01:32:42,280
我们从塔科马募集了92美元，以罗杰・莫里斯之名
We got $92 from Tacoma in honor of Roger Morris.

1525
01:32:42,300 --> 01:32:44,870
再加上从塞奎姆给乔・兰茨募集的75美元
$75 more from Sequim for Joe Rantz.

1526
01:32:45,140 --> 01:32:47,070
从奥林匹亚给唐・休姆募集的90美元
$90 from Olympia for Don Hume.

1527
01:32:47,730 --> 01:32:50,670
每个孩子的家乡都付出了努力
Every hometown of these boys has given somethin'.

1528
01:32:51,100 --> 01:32:53,670
太平洋电报公司今晚刚寄来250美元
Pacific Telegraph just sent $250 this evening.

1529
01:32:53,700 --> 01:32:54,830
我们一共筹集了
Where does that put us

1530
01:32:54,860 --> 01:32:55,790
多少了现在？
with everything else we've got?

1531
01:32:55,870 --> 01:32:57,440
－嗯，差不多了　－但是呢？
- Eh, close. - But?

1532
01:32:57,580 --> 01:32:59,340
好吧，接近就是接近，艾尔
Well, close is just close, Al.

1533
01:32:59,930 --> 01:33:01,520
我们没时间了
And we're out of time.

1534
01:33:04,340 --> 01:33:06,550
来吧
Come on.

1535
01:33:16,250 --> 01:33:19,280
乌尔布里克森太太，我来找你丈夫
Mrs. Ulbrickson, I'm looking for your husband.

1536
01:33:28,620 --> 01:33:30,310
我们还有四个小时呢，凯
We still got four hours, Ky.

1537
01:33:30,440 --> 01:33:32,770
像往常一样争分夺秒
Racing the clock as usual.

1538
01:33:33,380 --> 01:33:34,360
我不能骗你，艾尔
I can't lie to you, Al.

1539
01:33:34,390 --> 01:33:37,060
我的孩子们很想去柏林
My boys would love to go to Berlin.

1540
01:33:38,200 --> 01:33:39,600
你还缺多少？
How short are you?

1541
01:33:40,800 --> 01:33:42,070
300美金
$300.00

1542
01:33:42,490 --> 01:33:43,480
左右
Give or take.

1543
01:33:44,500 --> 01:33:45,490
嗯
Hmm.

1544
01:33:58,360 --> 01:33:59,570
可以吗？
May I?

1545
01:34:15,590 --> 01:34:17,430
这是来自加州熊队的
This is from the Cal Bears.

1546
01:34:19,450 --> 01:34:21,790
一张300美元的欠条
An IOU for $300.

1547
01:34:24,040 --> 01:34:25,310
或多或少
Give or take.

1548
01:34:33,040 --> 01:34:34,310
凯
Ky.

1549
01:34:38,680 --> 01:34:41,450
除了你的孩子们，没有人有资格去
No one deserves to go but your boys.

1550
01:34:44,890 --> 01:34:46,090
先生们
Gentlemen.

1551
01:34:46,930 --> 01:34:48,230
乌尔布里克森夫人
Mrs. Ulbrickson.

1552
01:34:50,040 --> 01:34:53,440
如果钱还有剩的话，你们可以给我带点纪念品回来
And if there's any extra, you can bring me back a souvenir.

1553
01:35:15,240 --> 01:35:17,070
登上，SS，曼哈顿号
Aboard the SS Manhattan,

1554
01:35:17,200 --> 01:35:19,700
一船美国运动员驶往汉堡
a shipload of American athletes sails for Hamburg.

1555
01:35:19,830 --> 01:35:21,840
奥林匹克运动会，他们的目标
The Olympic Games, their goal.

1556
01:35:22,090 --> 01:35:23,690
这是杰西・欧文斯
Here is Jesse Owens, 

1557
01:35:23,830 --> 01:35:26,570
俄亥俄大学的一个人组成的田径队
the one-man track team from the University of Ohio.

1558
01:35:26,840 --> 01:35:28,600
有人说是“有史以来最伟大的”
Some say, "The greatest ever."

1559
01:35:28,730 --> 01:35:31,400
300多名运动员将上岸
More than 300 athletes will march ashore

1560
01:35:31,540 --> 01:35:34,210
在德国的土地上，准备为金牌而战
on German soil, ready to fight for gold.

1561
01:35:34,780 --> 01:35:37,790
参与者包括华盛顿大学的
Among the participants are the University of Washington's

1562
01:35:37,880 --> 01:35:40,080
8人赛艇初级队
junior varsity eight-man rowing crew.

1563
01:35:40,650 --> 01:35:42,300
这艘小艇已经准备好
The boat is ready to do battle

1564
01:35:42,350 --> 01:35:44,390
与意大利、英国
with the likes of Italy, Great Britain

1565
01:35:44,520 --> 01:35:45,880
和德国等
and Germany,

1566
01:35:45,980 --> 01:35:48,610
最受欢迎的队伍一决高下
all favorites in this most grueling of events.

1567
01:35:49,190 --> 01:35:52,370
在柏林，奥运会的筹备工作已经完成
In Berlin, the preparations for the Games are complete, 

1568
01:35:52,450 --> 01:35:54,760
德国人民已经准备好欢迎
and the German people are ready to welcome

1569
01:35:54,830 --> 01:35:57,300
来自52个国家的运动员
athletes from 52 countries.

1570
01:35:57,740 --> 01:35:59,430
德国总理阿道夫・希特勒
German Chancellor Adolf Hitler

1571
01:35:59,530 --> 01:36:01,780
曾承诺要举办一场无与伦比的盛会
has promised a spectacle like no other, 

1572
01:36:01,810 --> 01:36:04,680
并计划出席各种活动
and plans to attend a variety of events.

1573
01:36:05,350 --> 01:36:07,780
在汉堡，成千上万的德国人欢呼雀跃
In Hamburg, thousands of cheering Germans

1574
01:36:07,810 --> 01:36:11,150
欢迎准备上岸的美国人
welcome the Americans as they ready to disembark.

1575
01:36:11,780 --> 01:36:13,370
这些业余运动员
These amateur athletes

1576
01:36:13,480 --> 01:36:15,670
他们为代表自己的国家做出了巨大牺牲
have sacrificed so much to represent their country, 

1577
01:36:15,930 --> 01:36:18,860
还有几天奥运会就要开幕了
and as the opening of the Games is just days away, 

1578
01:36:18,890 --> 01:36:20,580
海内外的美国人
Americans at home and abroad

1579
01:36:20,640 --> 01:36:23,800
期待为这些敬业的运动员们加油助威
look forward to rooting for these dedicated athletes.

1580
01:37:00,430 --> 01:37:02,060
你好
Hi.

1581
01:37:07,340 --> 01:37:08,330
好的
All right.

1582
01:37:12,410 --> 01:37:15,640
换好衣服，我们去看看航道
Get changed, we'll go look over the course.

1583
01:37:23,050 --> 01:37:24,420
这太棒了
This is great.

1584
01:37:24,440 --> 01:37:25,380
还不错
Not bad.

1585
01:37:26,400 --> 01:37:28,700
－这就够了　－比在老家强多了
- This'll do. - It's better than back home.

1586
01:37:31,050 --> 01:37:32,080
希特勒万岁
Heil Hitler.

1587
01:37:32,260 --> 01:37:33,970
记住阿拉莫
Remember the Alamo.

1588
01:37:36,570 --> 01:37:38,110
乔，开幕式
Joe, opening ceremony.

1589
01:37:38,130 --> 01:37:39,330
快点，你要迟到了
Come on, you're gonna be late.

1590
01:37:40,160 --> 01:37:41,700
我想我就不去了
I think I gotta skip.

1591
01:37:41,850 --> 01:37:43,220
我太累了
I'm just too tired.

1592
01:37:44,230 --> 01:37:46,000
怎么了，有什么问题吗，唐？
Why, what's the problem, Don?

1593
01:37:48,780 --> 01:37:50,210
唐感觉不太好
Don doesn't feel so great.

1594
01:38:07,830 --> 01:38:09,860
去和其他人会合吧，我留下
Go join the rest. I'll, uh... I'll stay.

1595
01:38:10,010 --> 01:38:13,380
我来殿后，你得和你的团队一起走
I'll hang back. You need to walk with your team.

1596
01:38:15,940 --> 01:38:17,210
谢谢你，乔治
Thanks, George.

1597
01:38:19,610 --> 01:38:21,280
好了，休息吧
All right, get some rest.

1598
01:38:21,710 --> 01:38:23,100
吃点东西吧
Try and eat somethin'.

1599
01:38:32,990 --> 01:38:34,720
匈牙利
Ungarn.

1600
01:38:50,270 --> 01:38:52,510
你是杰西，对吧？杰西・欧文斯？
You're Jesse, right? Jesse Owens?

1601
01:38:52,710 --> 01:38:53,910
我是
I am.

1602
01:38:54,260 --> 01:38:56,120
你真的是世界上跑得最快的人吗？
You really the fastest man in the world?

1603
01:38:56,520 --> 01:38:58,190
－我不知道　－这里的人说
- I don't know. - Folks around here say

1604
01:38:58,220 --> 01:38:59,640
你会赢下你参加的每一场比赛
you're gonna win every race you're in.

1605
01:38:59,780 --> 01:39:01,140
但愿如此
Well, I hope so.

1606
01:39:01,300 --> 01:39:03,100
给德国人点厉害瞧瞧，好吗？
Show those Germans what for, all right?

1607
01:39:03,480 --> 01:39:05,690
－不　－不
- No. - No?

1608
01:39:05,760 --> 01:39:07,100
不是给德国人
Not the Germans.

1609
01:39:07,990 --> 01:39:09,290
是给家乡的父老乡亲的
The folks back home.

1610
01:39:15,660 --> 01:39:17,830
美利坚合众国
United States of America.

1611
01:39:22,170 --> 01:39:23,670
匈牙利队
The Hungarian team

1612
01:39:23,810 --> 01:39:25,340
向德国领导人表示敬意
offering their respect to the German leader.

1613
01:39:25,840 --> 01:39:28,140
美国人来了
And here come the Americans.

1614
01:39:28,890 --> 01:39:31,690
美国没有敬礼
With no salute from the United States.

1615
01:39:32,940 --> 01:39:35,540
听起来孩子们正在交朋友
Sounds like the boys are making friends.

1616
01:39:39,890 --> 01:39:41,320
好了，起风了
All right, the winds are up.

1617
01:39:41,360 --> 01:39:44,260
这对我们有好处，你们在第二道不受直接影响
That's good for us. You're protected in lane two.

1618
01:39:44,740 --> 01:39:46,310
让其他更远的船
Let all the other boats farther out

1619
01:39:46,330 --> 01:39:47,630
去对付阵风吧
deal with the gusts.

1620
01:39:47,840 --> 01:39:50,150
鲍比，你越是紧守
Bobby, the tighter you hold the line,

1621
01:39:50,240 --> 01:39:51,480
比赛就越平稳
the smoother the ride.

1622
01:39:52,130 --> 01:39:53,690
现在是三场预赛
Now, three prelims.

1623
01:39:53,870 --> 01:39:56,890
每场预赛的获胜者将自动获得总决赛的入场券
The winner of each gets an automatic berth in the finals.

1624
01:39:56,970 --> 01:39:59,110
这就是你们想要的，休息一天
That is what you want. You want a day off

1625
01:39:59,210 --> 01:40:00,840
让其他球队疲于奔命
and let the other teams wear themselves out

1626
01:40:00,980 --> 01:40:02,040
多赛一场
with an extra race.

1627
01:40:02,180 --> 01:40:03,570
所以，不要保留
So, do not hold back.

1628
01:40:03,600 --> 01:40:05,700
英国队是我们这组值得关注的队伍
Great Britain's the team to watch in our heat.

1629
01:40:06,410 --> 01:40:08,580
鲍比，别再来波基普西那招了
Bobby, not another Poughkeepsie.

1630
01:40:08,820 --> 01:40:10,250
它们不会像加州队那样后程乏力的
They won't fade like Cal,

1631
01:40:10,280 --> 01:40:12,010
所以绝不能让他们领先超过两个艇位
so never let them get more than two lengths up.

1632
01:40:12,220 --> 01:40:14,210
伙计们，这是你们应得的
Fellas, you've earned this.

1633
01:40:15,020 --> 01:40:17,590
他们不会为风格颁发金牌
They don't give gold medals for style.

1634
01:40:17,890 --> 01:40:20,260
唯一重要的是你们在水上的速度有多快
All that matters is how fast you are on the water.

1635
01:40:21,060 --> 01:40:22,670
这里没人比你们更快
And nobody here is faster.

1636
01:40:32,140 --> 01:40:33,410
蹬腿！
Legs through!

1637
01:40:33,980 --> 01:40:35,670
美国人已经领先
And the Americans are already leading

1638
01:40:35,760 --> 01:40:37,230
大不列颠半个艇位
by half a boat over Great Britain

1639
01:40:37,340 --> 01:40:38,740
优势还在变大
and looking for more.

1640
01:40:38,820 --> 01:40:40,920
法国和捷克斯洛伐克紧随其后
Followed by France and Czechoslovakia.

1641
01:40:45,540 --> 01:40:48,540
破，划！破，划！
In, through! In, through!

1642
01:40:49,680 --> 01:40:51,380
领桨员冉・劳里
Stroke Ran Laurie

1643
01:40:51,410 --> 01:40:52,880
正在疯狂地挖掘英国艇的速度
is digging furiously for the British boat.

1644
01:40:52,930 --> 01:40:54,230
但是美国人
But the Americans

1645
01:40:54,250 --> 01:40:56,340
现在正在大举进攻，扩大领先优势
are pouring it on now, extending their lead.

1646
01:40:56,950 --> 01:40:59,280
抬头，破，划
Eyes up. In, through!

1647
01:40:59,870 --> 01:41:01,140
划
And through!

1648
01:41:01,540 --> 01:41:03,160
只剩100米了
And with only 100 meters to go, 

1649
01:41:03,220 --> 01:41:06,260
美国人可能正在接近奥运会纪录
the Americans could be closing in on an Olympic record.

1650
01:41:06,440 --> 01:41:07,430
抬头
Eyes up!

1651
01:41:11,580 --> 01:41:13,310
6分8秒
Six minutes point eight seconds.

1652
01:41:13,450 --> 01:41:14,950
新的奥运纪录！
A new Olympic record!

1653
01:41:15,060 --> 01:41:16,690
美国赢了！
The United States has won!

1654
01:41:19,240 --> 01:41:20,970
你还好吗？嘿，你知道我们赢了吗？
You all right? Hey, you know we won?

1655
01:41:21,020 --> 01:41:23,320
－唐，你还好吗？－你知道我们赢了，对吧？嗯？
- Don, are you okay? - You know we won, right? Huh?

1656
01:41:23,460 --> 01:41:24,960
－嘿　－来吧
- Hey. - Come on. Come on.

1657
01:41:25,040 --> 01:41:26,040
精彩的比赛
Good race.

1658
01:41:26,060 --> 01:41:27,770
奥运纪录是个好的开始
Olympic record's a nice start.

1659
01:41:27,900 --> 01:41:30,330
但这一切只是为了让我们进入真正重要的比赛
But all that does is get us into the race that matters.

1660
01:41:30,410 --> 01:41:33,650
